?? 4/13/23 Weekly Update Highlights:

?? zkSync Era Integration
This week, we’ve integrated several new blockchains and increased our number of supported networks to 42. Rubic.exchange has successfully integrated zkSync Era via Symbiosis and Multichain as Providers, making it the fifth Layer 2 (L2) network and the first ZK-rollup solution to be integrated into Rubic’s ecosystem, among 40+ other networks! Additionally, we’re in the process of integrating Mute.io as a DEX for zkSync Era.
Check out the zkSync Era dashboard here.

?? Astar Integration
This week, we have also integrated the Astar network.
Cross-chain swaps for the non-EVM Astar are conducted via ChangeNow as a provider, while the EVM version of Astar is integrated via the ArthSwap DEX and Multichain Bridge. This integration became possible thanks to Rubic winning the Web3 Incubation Program by Sony Network and Astar.

?? Upcoming Integrations
SDK Update: Since Rubic’s contracts have been switched back on, our SDK integrators will soon be able to resume charging fees for swaps.

ChangeNOW New Chains: Currently, we are working on adding even more chains to Rubic through ChangeNOW as a provider. Matter Labs released the ZK Stack for building Hyperchains alongside zkSync Era

Matter Labs has released the ZK Stack, a codebase for building networks using the technology of zkSync Era. The goal is to create a network of interconnected blockchains, called Hyperchains, using zero-knowledge proofs. Developers who build Hyperchains can choose to create Layer 2 networks that run parallel to zkSync Era, or Layer 3 networks that run on top of it. Hyperchains can be connected together using Hyperbridges. Matter Labs expects the first Hyperchains to go live this year.

ZKsync [ZK] will conduct initial listing on Binance and multiple other exchanges today, on June 17th 

ZKsync $ZK will be initially listed on Binance, KuCoin, Bybit, OKX, Gate, MEXC and other exchanges today, June 17th, starting at 8:00 UTC. Moreover, Binance is offering 10.5M ZK tokens airdrop to up to 52,500 Binance users who meet certain criteria. Previously, ZKsync has announced 3.675B $ZK token airdrop (17.5% of total supply) to 695,232 eligible wallet addresses. Eligibility and allocations for the airdrop were based on a snapshot of activity on ZKsync Era and ZKsync Lite taken on March 24th.

Users will be available to claim their tokens on June 17th, at 7:00 UTC here ?? claim.zknation.io

ZKsync is a trustless Layer 2 protocol for scalable low-cost payments on Ethereum, powered by zkRollup technology. Its main network, zkSync Era, has around $762M in assets deposited.
